    summary:"Frank Werner Maiwald, 61, died July 4, 2024 in Los Angeles. He was a JPL technical group supervisor who managed the development of the SBG-VSWIR instrument, a visible shortwave infrared spectrometer with direct dual-use civilian and classified defence applications, and had previously overseen instrument delivery for the AMR-C, COWVR, AMR/Jason 3, and HIFI programs. His obituary contains no cause of death, no mention of illness, and no decline narrative. Authorities confirmed no autopsy was performed. No press release from JPL. No memorial from NASA. No Caltech acknowledgment. No local news coverage. No entry in the LA County Medical Examiner's public database. He was a longtime JPL colleague of Michael David Hicks, who had died in the same city under the same circumstances of institutional silence eleven months earlier. He died eleven months before JPL colleague Monica Reza vanished.",
