    affiliations:["novartis","dod"],
    summary:"Jason Thomas, 45, assistant director of chemical biology at Novartis Institutes for BioMedical Research in Cambridge, Massachusetts, was reported missing on December 13, 2025, two days before Nuno Loureiro was shot at his Brookline home. He left on foot. His phone and wallet were left behind. His research focused on developing new medicines including potential cancer treatments, and he held active contracts with the Department of Defence through Novartis. In March 2026, a body recovered from Lake Quannapowitt in Wakefield was believed to be his. Investigators stated they did not suspect foul play. He had recently lost both parents, who died within an hour of each other. He is documented here with a clear caveat: he sits at the edge of this pattern, not at its centre. The most likely explanation, given the documented personal context, is personal tragedy.",
